The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 River link

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Bhubaneswar, May 15: The Orissa government has okayed a proposal to inter-link Vansadhara and Rushikulya rivers at a cost of around Rs 600 crore.

 The decision was taken at a recent meeting chaired by chief minister Naveen Patnaik. While giving his consent to the river project, Patnaik directed officials of the water resources department to prepare a detailed report.

 The catchment area of the river is spread over 1,400 sq km in Orissa and 300 sq km in Andhra Pradesh. A controversy has brewing ever since the Andhra Pradesh government decided to construct canals and reservoirs without consulting its counterpart in Orissa, allegedly violating a water-sharing agreement 




